snippet.textDisplay: Yeah i agree Chael. One thing that’s always been great about each time these guys are going to fight is that Tony has never looked intimidated, he’s always has had the same calmness after having to study Khabib. So yeah , it’s because he’s spent his life having answers for this particular opponent, he doesn’t see him as the scary champ because he’s stood in his face long before that. Tony knows he’s the guy who can stop 3-4 of the things that Khabib has to do to get to that place of control and to throw a monkey wrench of surprise. Tony also is a master on his back and the master of these surprise squirrelly moves that leave people in shock/frustrated for a second. If Khabib gets frustrated he’s done, if he is stopped in his steps of the ingredients he needs to do what he always does then he becomes prey for Tony. Tony is winning a lot and is doing all sorts of different stuff and we will see more because he has answers for this opponent. There’s no better opponent for Tony for the belt than Khabib —Tony is designed for this. He also has a slight height advantage which I’ve always believed is 1 advantage anyone has along with any grappling skills on Khabib. And we know that is why Khabib cuts 3 divisions-he won’t dare go up against taller guys because wrapping the legs and reaching the face won’t work. I honestly think Khabib would be easy for Diaz standing and on the ground.  I believe Tony shuts Khabib down and i also think Conor would take the rematch. You don’t have to be an amazing grappler to beat him. Striking can take out a grappler. We forget Ronda , but Rondas head wasn’t in it either. She got stopped by 2 strikers but, then Meisha goes and beats Holly, we know Ronda beat Meisha oh yeah twice! And off the top of my head there were at least 2 opponents who beat Amanda that Ronda beat. So point is Tony has everything you would need to be Khabib and yeah you can be a great striker and take out a great grappler and that will be Conor if Tony doesn’t do it. Bye Bye Khabib hide location!

snippet.textDisplay: How do you then explain Chael him taking down Conor and Al Iaquinta in basically the center of the Octagon?? And with Conor, he was on the back foot, which is even harder. I think that guy is so good and unstoppable, he shoots so fast and it doesn't really matter if he is in the open or got you on the fence. Yes, we can all see and acknowledge that he does his best work when he pushes his opponent's back against the fence, him and his father perfected that style of wrestling for YEARS which is the most suitable for MMA, but he shoots so fast and is faster than anyone trying to defend from being taken down by him. Conor might've survived and the fight might've gone a little different if he didn't throw that knee on Khabib's entry, which helped Khabib take him down eventually. As someone says, Khabib only needs your pinky toe to cling on to you. It's ridiculous. He may be a little less effective when in the open space and in that center of the Octagon as you point out Chael. But man oh man, he will take you down no matter what. It's really interesting the level of skill and determination that guy has. Never seen anything like it in the sport of MMA. Him and Jones are for me the greatest fighters ever, because Jon has so many tools and is so calm, has such an unwavering winner's mentality, and Khabib is just mentally bulletproof and determined as nobody else is + grappling prowess which have been honed and sharpen since the age of 3. IMO, if he beats Tony, I really can't see anyone beating him. Justin Gaethje has got a good style and styles make fights but Khabib IMO has basically a better cardio and a better work rate. And wrestling is not the same as grappling all in all. If they end up on the ground, which they most likely will - Khabib will pass guard and start to throw bombs and destroy Justin. That's what I think would happen anyways. The only guy that weighs 155 and can possibly beat Khabib is Islam Makhachaev, his best friend and life long teammate and sparring partner. Some say he is Khabib but with a better stand up game and kickboxing. He might just beat Khabib, cause he knows all of his tricks and seems a sharper fighter standing up. That will never happen of course, cause they'll never want to fight each other, they're brothers basically.
